  "body": "Hi there,\r\n\r\nI upgraded my full node from 1.8.23 to 1.9.9 on Dec. 6(Because the old one can not sync. blocks any more)\r\n\r\n**I was shocked**: the disk usage increased to **616GB** at a \"visible speed\"\r\n\r\nInfact,  I found that a newly synced full node will use less disk space than one which has been running for a long time. \r\n\r\nSo I guess there's some data can be deleted, is there a way to shrink the chaindata?\r\n",
